1
00:00:19.686 --> 00:00:23.440 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I never imagined someone</i>
<i>could be so honest and direct.</i>

2
00:00:25.108 --> 00:00:29.070 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>She looked me straight in the eye</i>
<i>and told me I wasn't scary.</i>

3
00:00:30.029 --> 00:00:32.115 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Ms. Waguri, a regular at our patisserie.</i>

4
00:00:33.700 --> 00:00:36.202 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>But I never would've guessed…</i>

5
00:00:40.290 --> 00:00:44.002 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>that she is a student at Kikyo.</i>

6
00:01:00.643 --> 00:01:07.609 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
THE FRAGRANT FLOWER BLOOMS WITH DIGNITY

7
00:02:19.347 --> 00:02:20.849 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Morning!

8
00:02:21.766 --> 00:02:24.561 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I can't take it anymore!

9
00:02:25.728 --> 00:02:26.813 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Take what?

10
00:02:26.896 --> 00:02:30.608 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Kikyo! I'm talking about Kikyo!
They gave me that death stare again today!

11
00:02:30.692 --> 00:02:31.943 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Isn't that every day?

12
00:02:32.026 --> 00:02:35.071 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's right! But even I've got my limits.

13
00:02:35.155 --> 00:02:38.324 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Seriously, what's their deal?

14
00:02:41.411 --> 00:02:45.498 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's not like Chidori was my first choice!

15
00:02:45.582 --> 00:02:47.876 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
More like it was the only school
that'd take you, right?

16
00:02:47.959 --> 00:02:48.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The heck?

17
00:02:49.502 --> 00:02:52.505 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're lucky it's you two. Saku and Ayato.

18
00:02:52.589 --> 00:02:54.549 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Morning.
-Morning!

19
00:02:54.632 --> 00:02:57.343 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Listen, you gotta hear this!

20
00:02:57.427 --> 00:03:00.054 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Shohei, where do you get all that energy?

21
00:03:00.138 --> 00:03:01.890 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You talking about Kikyo?

22
00:03:02.473 --> 00:03:04.392 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We got the same death stare.

23
00:03:04.976 --> 00:03:07.520 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If even Mr. Popular Saku
is getting iced out, we're screwed.

24
00:03:08.605 --> 00:03:10.732 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Kikyo? No thanks.

25
00:03:12.150 --> 00:03:15.153 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I mean, you've got the rich girls at Kikyo
and the idiots at Chidori…

26
00:03:16.029 --> 00:03:19.115 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Any way you slice it, we just don't mix.

27
00:03:19.616 --> 00:03:22.243 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, I know! Like adding fuel to a fire!

28
00:03:22.327 --> 00:03:23.369 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
More like oil and water.

29
00:03:23.453 --> 00:03:26.456 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Huh?
-Anyway, what happened to your forehead?

30
00:03:27.457 --> 00:03:28.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And he's not listening.

31
00:03:29.083 --> 00:03:31.294 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He said he hit his head or something.

32
00:03:31.377 --> 00:03:32.795 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How do you even manage that?

33
00:03:33.796 --> 00:03:36.925 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Wait, did you close
those curtains, Rintaro?

34
00:03:37.008 --> 00:03:39.302 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh? What?

35
00:03:39.928 --> 00:03:41.971 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just thought it was rare
to see them closed.

36
00:03:42.472 --> 00:03:43.306 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah.

37
00:03:43.389 --> 00:03:46.309 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Shoot, I left them closed.</i>

38
00:03:47.060 --> 00:03:50.813 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I mean, staring at Kikyo's building
isn't exactly gonna lift your mood, is it?

39
00:03:50.897 --> 00:03:52.982 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's not about that!

40
00:03:55.276 --> 00:03:58.154 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's with you all of a sudden?

41
00:04:00.365 --> 00:04:02.533 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My bad. Forget it.

42
00:04:03.034 --> 00:04:05.119 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The sun was just kinda bright, that's all.

43
00:04:05.620 --> 00:04:09.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But you never close them.
You said you like the warmth.

44
00:04:09.749 --> 00:04:11.834 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, sometimes I feel like closing them.

45
00:04:13.795 --> 00:04:17.215 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Therefore, when referring
to a person or thing,

46
00:04:17.799 --> 00:04:21.010 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you add a phrase such as "that person"
or "that thing" after the noun.

47
00:04:21.094 --> 00:04:22.720 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Ms. Waguri…</i>

48
00:04:22.804 --> 00:04:25.056 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>She looked really surprised earlier.</i>

49
00:04:25.556 --> 00:04:29.018 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I closed the curtains</i>
<i>without even thinking.</i>

50
00:04:29.102 --> 00:04:31.604 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>But now that I think about it,</i>
<i>I must've seemed really rude.</i>

51
00:04:34.941 --> 00:04:37.986 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Kikyo and Chidori, huh…</i>

52
00:04:38.069 --> 00:04:40.738 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I doubt she'll come to the shop again.</i>

53
00:04:43.157 --> 00:04:45.243 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Maybe it's better this way.</i>

54
00:04:45.326 --> 00:04:48.913 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Nothing good would come</i>
<i>from getting involved with me.</i>

55
00:04:48.997 --> 00:04:50.540 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Especially since she's from Kikyo.</i>

56
00:04:52.542 --> 00:04:54.585 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>This is for the best.</i>

57
00:04:55.795 --> 00:04:57.463 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>This is how it should be.</i>

58
00:04:59.966 --> 00:05:00.967 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, Rintaro.

59
00:05:01.467 --> 00:05:04.721 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You free today? Let's go hang out.

60
00:05:05.430 --> 00:05:06.764 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well…

61
00:05:08.474 --> 00:05:11.394 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Looks like there's no request</i>
<i>for help from Mom.</i>

62
00:05:12.478 --> 00:05:13.980 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sure, where are we going?

63
00:05:14.063 --> 00:05:16.524 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No way! You're actually down!

64
00:05:16.607 --> 00:05:17.775 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah, I guess.

65
00:05:19.235 --> 00:05:22.196 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Gonna sing my heart out
to make up for missing last time.

66
00:05:22.280 --> 00:05:23.948 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've got a coupon for free fries.

67
00:05:24.032 --> 00:05:25.783 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Fries it is!

68
00:05:25.867 --> 00:05:30.163 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Hope we score over 95 today.
-Leave it to me!

69
00:05:30.246 --> 00:05:35.543 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've been practicing a new song.
Feels like today's the day.

70
00:05:37.587 --> 00:05:39.589 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's with all the commotion?

71
00:05:40.882 --> 00:05:42.592 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Lemme see too!
-For real?

72
00:05:42.675 --> 00:05:45.344 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Well, that's new.
-Who is she waiting for?

73
00:05:45.428 --> 00:05:46.763 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's up?

74
00:05:48.222 --> 00:05:51.225 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, well, it's just…

75
00:05:53.352 --> 00:05:54.896 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There's a girl waiting there.

76
00:05:57.482 --> 00:05:58.900 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Ms. Waguri?!</i>

77
00:06:00.610 --> 00:06:03.863 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Why's she standing here? What's she doing?</i>

78
00:06:05.573 --> 00:06:07.575 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, hey, hey!

79
00:06:08.076 --> 00:06:11.370 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's a Kikyo girl doing at Chidori?!

80
00:06:12.789 --> 00:06:13.873 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>That idiot!</i>

81
00:06:13.956 --> 00:06:18.252 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He's lashing out at her
just 'cause she's from Kikyo.

82
00:06:22.381 --> 00:06:24.008 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm waiting for someone.

83
00:06:24.092 --> 00:06:27.345 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh? And who exactly are you waiting for?

84
00:06:29.347 --> 00:06:30.556 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Usami.

85
00:06:31.099 --> 00:06:32.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Quit scaring her.

86
00:06:35.520 --> 00:06:36.521 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sorry.

87
00:06:38.106 --> 00:06:39.732 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's okay.

88
00:06:40.817 --> 00:06:44.946 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Says she's waiting.
Does she know someone from Chidori?

89
00:06:46.322 --> 00:06:48.991 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The hell?

90
00:06:54.622 --> 00:06:56.374 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm so friggin' jealous!

91
00:06:56.999 --> 00:06:59.001 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Huh?
-I can't stand Kikyo,

92
00:06:59.085 --> 00:07:02.046 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but having your girl
waiting for you at the school gate?

93
00:07:02.130 --> 00:07:05.758 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dammit! I want a girlfriend too!

94
00:07:05.842 --> 00:07:07.009 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Good thing he's an idiot.</i>

95
00:07:07.885 --> 00:07:08.970 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Kaoruko!

96
00:07:09.470 --> 00:07:11.180 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What are you doing?

97
00:07:11.722 --> 00:07:14.142 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ayu, Suzuka…

98
00:07:15.560 --> 00:07:17.770 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You shouldn't be here. Let's hurry back.

99
00:07:17.854 --> 00:07:20.189 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-But…
-No buts!

100
00:07:20.273 --> 00:07:23.985 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Seriously?
What is she doing over at Chidori?

101
00:07:24.068 --> 00:07:26.279 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She might catch Chidori's stupidity.

102
00:07:26.362 --> 00:07:27.738 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's Kikyo.

103
00:07:27.822 --> 00:07:29.740 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They're talking smack about us again.

104
00:07:29.824 --> 00:07:32.076 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Good thing Hoshina's not here to see this.

105
00:07:32.785 --> 00:07:33.870 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come on, let's go.

106
00:07:36.581 --> 00:07:37.415 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey!

107
00:07:37.915 --> 00:07:40.334 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You bumped into me.
Least you can do is apologize!

108
00:07:44.130 --> 00:07:45.756 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come on, Kaoruko.

109
00:07:47.884 --> 00:07:49.677 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey! Get back here, Kikyo!

110
00:07:50.636 --> 00:07:53.431 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll remember this!

111
00:07:56.350 --> 00:07:59.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Dammit! Why am I the only one
who has to take that crap?

112
00:07:59.896 --> 00:08:03.649 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, you did go in guns blazing.

113
00:08:04.233 --> 00:08:06.819 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I wonder what that girl even wanted.

114
00:08:06.903 --> 00:08:10.323 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Like I care! This is why
I can't stand those Kikyo girls!

115
00:08:12.033 --> 00:08:13.910 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Man, that was seriously close.</i>

116
00:08:16.579 --> 00:08:18.331 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Wait, hold on…</i>

117
00:08:18.873 --> 00:08:21.876 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Does that mean she came to see me?</i>

118
00:08:22.502 --> 00:08:23.836 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>No, no, no.</i>

119
00:08:23.920 --> 00:08:26.005 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>She might know someone else from Chidori!</i>

120
00:08:27.465 --> 00:08:30.176 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>But if that really were the case…</i>

121
00:08:31.552 --> 00:08:33.679 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, Rintaro, don't you agree--

122
00:08:34.889 --> 00:08:37.725 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dude, what's with the weird face?!

123
00:08:37.808 --> 00:08:38.768 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh?

124
00:08:38.851 --> 00:08:41.771 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
True. Never seen that look before.

125
00:08:41.854 --> 00:08:43.648 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's even scarier than usual.

126
00:08:44.190 --> 00:08:45.191 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Shut up!

127
00:08:45.274 --> 00:08:48.110 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jeez, don't scare me like that!

128
00:08:48.194 --> 00:08:50.321 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's because you keep making him worry.

129
00:08:50.404 --> 00:08:52.657 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Wait, how is it my fault?!

130
00:08:52.740 --> 00:08:53.824 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>What is this?</i>

131
00:08:55.076 --> 00:08:57.286 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I'm not sure why, but…</i>

132
00:08:58.829 --> 00:09:00.289 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I feel happy.</i>

133
00:09:02.375 --> 00:09:04.168 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>No, no! What am I thinking?</i>

134
00:09:04.252 --> 00:09:06.462 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>All I did was scare her off again.</i>

135
00:09:07.797 --> 00:09:10.967 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We obviously shouldn't</i>
<i>see each other again.</i>

136
00:09:21.936 --> 00:09:24.772 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You put in the next song, Rintaro?

137
00:09:24.855 --> 00:09:27.692 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, my bad. I'll add it now.

138
00:09:27.775 --> 00:09:28.609 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All good.

139
00:09:35.199 --> 00:09:37.743 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dammit! I can't even hit 90!

140
00:09:37.827 --> 00:09:38.911 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But you sang well!

141
00:09:38.995 --> 00:09:40.454 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Doesn't matter without the score!

142
00:09:40.538 --> 00:09:42.623 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, Rintaro.

143
00:09:43.624 --> 00:09:45.293 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Did something happen recently?

144
00:09:47.420 --> 00:09:48.254 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh?

145
00:09:48.337 --> 00:09:49.797 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is that so?

146
00:09:49.880 --> 00:09:53.884 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yeah, you've been acting
kinda strange today too.

147
00:09:54.552 --> 00:09:57.513 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If something's on your mind,
you can talk to us.

148
00:09:58.681 --> 00:10:02.226 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That injury doesn't look like
you just bumped it by accident.

149
00:10:09.942 --> 00:10:10.901 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Should I tell them?</i>

150
00:10:12.236 --> 00:10:15.781 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>But why even bring up Ms. Waguri?</i>

151
00:10:16.741 --> 00:10:18.826 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>What's the point?</i>

152
00:10:20.661 --> 00:10:22.955 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Even if I did tell them,</i>
<i>they'd probably just say…</i>

153
00:10:24.040 --> 00:10:25.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Kikyo, huh…

154
00:10:25.416 --> 00:10:26.626 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I hate Kikyo.

155
00:10:26.709 --> 00:10:29.128 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don't waste your time
with those Kikyo girls.

156
00:10:30.087 --> 00:10:31.881 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I get why they'd say that…</i>

157
00:10:33.382 --> 00:10:34.508 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>but still…</i>

158
00:10:35.885 --> 00:10:37.345 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I don't want to hear it.</i>

159
00:10:38.846 --> 00:10:41.849 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nah, it's nothing. I'm good.

160
00:10:42.767 --> 00:10:43.768 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Right.

161
00:10:43.851 --> 00:10:46.520 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, if anything's up,
you can always talk to us.

162
00:10:50.358 --> 00:10:53.194 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Anyway, let's lighten things up
with the next song.

163
00:10:53.277 --> 00:10:55.696 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Wait, I didn't add anything yet.

164
00:10:55.780 --> 00:10:58.908 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I did it for you.
Get ready to hit the high notes!

165
00:10:58.991 --> 00:11:00.868 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh? You trying to kill me?

166
00:11:00.951 --> 00:11:02.036 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Here's your mic!

167
00:11:04.997 --> 00:11:06.582 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Natsusawa.
-Yeah?

168
00:11:07.083 --> 00:11:09.752 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sorry for making you worry.

169
00:11:13.047 --> 00:11:15.257 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is exactly what I mean, Rintaro.

170
00:11:15.341 --> 00:11:16.467 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh?

171
00:11:16.550 --> 00:11:17.676 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll join in.

172
00:11:17.760 --> 00:11:20.054 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Hand me a mic.
-What? You're gonna sing?

173
00:11:20.137 --> 00:11:21.389 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Talk about a rare treat!

174
00:11:27.395 --> 00:11:28.729 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My throat hurts.

175
00:11:29.480 --> 00:11:30.398 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh?

176
00:11:31.399 --> 00:11:33.859 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They're supposed to be
way past closing time…

177
00:11:37.988 --> 00:11:39.573 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm home.

178
00:11:39.657 --> 00:11:41.951 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, the shop door's unlocked.

179
00:11:45.704 --> 00:11:46.914 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Rintaro!

180
00:11:48.207 --> 00:11:49.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Welcome back.

181
00:11:51.752 --> 00:11:55.965 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
THE FRAGRANT FLOWER BLOOMS WITH DIGNITY

182
00:11:56.966 --> 00:11:59.218 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ms. Waguri? Why are you here?

183
00:11:59.301 --> 00:12:01.220 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm so sorry!

184
00:12:01.303 --> 00:12:03.556 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I caused such a scene.

185
00:12:03.639 --> 00:12:06.976 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
All because I underestimated just how bad
things are between Chidori and Kikyo.

186
00:12:07.059 --> 00:12:10.271 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What? That doesn't bother me at all.

187
00:12:10.354 --> 00:12:12.648 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Please, no need to bow like that.

188
00:12:12.731 --> 00:12:15.359 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Finally! Took you long enough!

189
00:12:15.443 --> 00:12:16.652 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Welcome home.

190
00:12:17.153 --> 00:12:18.154 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thanks.

191
00:12:18.237 --> 00:12:21.532 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You could've at least texted
if you were gonna be late!

192
00:12:21.615 --> 00:12:23.868 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Ms. Waguri's been waiting here
this whole time!

193
00:12:23.951 --> 00:12:24.869 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh?

194
00:12:24.952 --> 00:12:26.495 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ms. Waguri.

195
00:12:26.579 --> 00:12:30.040 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you still have time,
would you like some of our leftover cake?

196
00:12:30.124 --> 00:12:32.793 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you, but I should be heading off--

197
00:12:39.550 --> 00:12:42.052 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm sorry. That was so improper of me…

198
00:12:43.596 --> 00:12:45.306 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not you too, Rintaro.

199
00:12:47.099 --> 00:12:49.602 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sorry, sorry! My bad!

200
00:12:49.685 --> 00:12:50.895 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ms. Waguri.

201
00:12:52.813 --> 00:12:55.274 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How about we have some cake together?

202
00:12:57.902 --> 00:12:58.861 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Okay.

203
00:13:08.954 --> 00:13:11.832 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>She always looks so happy</i>
<i>when she's eating.</i>

204
00:13:11.916 --> 00:13:13.459 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
By the way…

205
00:13:13.542 --> 00:13:17.254 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is your friend okay? Did he hurt his chin?

206
00:13:17.338 --> 00:13:19.632 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, you mean Usami?

207
00:13:19.715 --> 00:13:22.051 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don't worry about him. He's tough.

208
00:13:22.551 --> 00:13:24.220 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm glad.

209
00:13:28.849 --> 00:13:31.477 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
By the way, what were you doing
at our school gate?

210
00:13:33.062 --> 00:13:36.232 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, I wanted to see you, Rintaro.

211
00:13:37.358 --> 00:13:38.984 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>So she was there because of me!</i>

212
00:13:39.068 --> 00:13:42.279 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But I won't be so careless again.

213
00:13:42.363 --> 00:13:43.739 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sorry.

214
00:13:43.822 --> 00:13:46.617 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don't be!
It was my schoolmates who instigated it.

215
00:13:46.700 --> 00:13:52.665 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Besides, seeing you there
made me really… happy. I mean…

216
00:13:54.500 --> 00:13:56.252 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Shoot! I just blurted it out!</i>

217
00:13:56.335 --> 00:13:59.004 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Wait! Sorry about that!
That was kinda creepy, wasn't it?

218
00:13:59.088 --> 00:14:00.214 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I take it back!

219
00:14:00.297 --> 00:14:01.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh? No!

220
00:14:01.840 --> 00:14:03.509 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don't take it back!

221
00:14:10.975 --> 00:14:14.228 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Aren't you going to eat any cake?

222
00:14:14.311 --> 00:14:16.647 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh? Yes! Let's eat!

223
00:14:16.730 --> 00:14:20.568 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You know, I wasn't expecting you
to stop by the shop today!

224
00:14:20.651 --> 00:14:22.403 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Because I showed up out of the blue?

225
00:14:22.486 --> 00:14:26.073 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No, I thought
you wouldn't come by anymore.

226
00:14:30.744 --> 00:14:31.954 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why?

227
00:14:32.037 --> 00:14:33.873 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh? I mean…

228
00:14:34.748 --> 00:14:36.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're from Chidori and Kikyo, right?

229
00:14:37.626 --> 00:14:39.503 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Since you're from Kikyo,

230
00:14:39.587 --> 00:14:42.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I thought you wouldn't want
to see me anymore.

231
00:14:44.341 --> 00:14:47.136 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Besides, nothing good would come
from getting involved with me--

232
00:14:47.219 --> 00:14:48.387 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But I…

233
00:14:49.263 --> 00:14:51.056 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
was happy…

234
00:14:52.266 --> 00:14:55.269 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
when I found out you went to Chidori.

235
00:14:57.146 --> 00:14:57.980 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What?

236
00:14:58.063 --> 00:15:00.149 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, look at the time!

237
00:15:01.150 --> 00:15:03.569 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sorry, I should head home now.

238
00:15:07.448 --> 00:15:09.074 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ms. Waguri!

239
00:15:11.452 --> 00:15:13.203 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's true.

240
00:15:13.913 --> 00:15:18.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I thought it'd be a chance
to get to know you better.

241
00:15:18.792 --> 00:15:20.920 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Ms. Wa--
-Thank you for the cake!

242
00:15:32.389 --> 00:15:34.308 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Why'd she make that face?</i>

243
00:15:35.768 --> 00:15:37.019 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I don't get it.</i>

244
00:15:37.519 --> 00:15:38.979 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I don't get it, but…</i>

245
00:15:40.397 --> 00:15:42.399 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I hurt her.</i>

246
00:15:45.861 --> 00:15:48.238 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh? Rintaro!

247
00:15:48.322 --> 00:15:50.532 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Did Ms. Waguri go home already?

248
00:15:51.825 --> 00:15:53.535 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, you listening?

249
00:15:57.957 --> 00:16:02.169 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Are you okay?!
I don't recall giving birth to a skeleton!

250
00:16:02.252 --> 00:16:04.630 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Just come with me, right now!

251
00:16:10.511 --> 00:16:11.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I see…

252
00:16:12.262 --> 00:16:13.722 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So that's what happened.

253
00:16:19.019 --> 00:16:21.981 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That friggin' hurt!

254
00:16:22.064 --> 00:16:23.524 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
First off…

255
00:16:23.607 --> 00:16:26.110 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You've gotta go chase after Ms. Waguri.

256
00:16:26.193 --> 00:16:30.155 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's dangerous for a girl to walk home
alone at night. You just learned that!

257
00:16:32.282 --> 00:16:33.450 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Seriously…

258
00:16:35.577 --> 00:16:39.748 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Ms. Waguri said she was happy
to get to know me.

259
00:16:40.916 --> 00:16:42.751 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't get what's going on anymore.

260
00:16:44.294 --> 00:16:46.714 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>This dense son of mine.</i>

261
00:16:48.298 --> 00:16:51.176 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where did I go wrong?

262
00:16:51.260 --> 00:16:52.219 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What?

263
00:16:57.057 --> 00:16:59.184 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-You know…
-Huh?

264
00:16:59.268 --> 00:17:02.938 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why would she want to see me
when she's from Kikyo?

265
00:17:04.690 --> 00:17:07.735 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do you really not get it?

266
00:17:07.818 --> 00:17:08.902 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Get what?

267
00:17:10.195 --> 00:17:13.365 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You're doing to her exactly what people
have done to you all your life.

268
00:17:15.576 --> 00:17:19.246 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You've always hated being judged
just by your appearance, right?

269
00:17:19.329 --> 00:17:22.624 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And yet now, all you do is harp on
about Kikyo this, Kikyo that.

270
00:17:23.333 --> 00:17:25.753 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Did Ms. Waguri ever treat you differently

271
00:17:25.836 --> 00:17:28.088 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
after she found out you were from Chidori?

272
00:17:29.131 --> 00:17:31.967 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But you,
what about her are you focusing on?

273
00:17:33.469 --> 00:17:37.389 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Nothing good would come</i>
<i>from getting involved with me.</i>

274
00:17:37.473 --> 00:17:40.142 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I heard his family runs a cake shop.

275
00:17:40.225 --> 00:17:41.894 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Totally doesn't fit his vibe.

276
00:17:41.977 --> 00:17:44.396 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He's got a reputation
for being terrifying.

277
00:17:45.355 --> 00:17:49.109 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Since you're from Kikyo.</i>

278
00:17:53.489 --> 00:17:55.282 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, are you listening?

279
00:17:58.494 --> 00:18:01.663 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh? What on earth are you doing?!

280
00:18:01.747 --> 00:18:03.040 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Tissue! Tissue!

281
00:18:04.875 --> 00:18:06.585 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I'm the worst.</i>

282
00:18:08.003 --> 00:18:12.007 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I'm no different from them.</i>
<i>What they did to me… I did to Ms. Waguri.</i>

283
00:18:15.135 --> 00:18:16.678 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Mom.
-Huh?

284
00:18:20.766 --> 00:18:22.142 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thanks.

285
00:18:31.985 --> 00:18:32.986 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh?

286
00:18:36.698 --> 00:18:38.200 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Rintaro?

287
00:18:39.701 --> 00:18:40.786 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What are you doing here?

288
00:18:42.412 --> 00:18:45.374 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I figured I'd see you
if I showed up early.

289
00:18:47.334 --> 00:18:48.418 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ms. Waguri.

290
00:18:48.502 --> 00:18:50.462 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes.

291
00:18:53.006 --> 00:18:54.633 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm sorry I hurt you yesterday.

292
00:18:56.426 --> 00:18:57.344 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm sorry.

293
00:18:58.220 --> 00:18:59.596 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hurt me?

294
00:19:01.598 --> 00:19:03.976 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You looked sad when you left last night.

295
00:19:14.278 --> 00:19:16.655 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's the matter?

296
00:19:19.992 --> 00:19:23.954 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Knowing I made that sort of face,
it's just so embarrassing.

297
00:19:26.623 --> 00:19:29.418 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's true I was sad.

298
00:19:29.501 --> 00:19:31.920 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But those were my own selfish feelings…

299
00:19:33.255 --> 00:19:37.885 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And I left without saying a word,
which only caused you more worry.

300
00:19:37.968 --> 00:19:39.094 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm so sorry!

301
00:19:39.678 --> 00:19:41.597 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don't be! I'm the one who…

302
00:19:44.099 --> 00:19:47.477 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're way too kind, Rintaro.

303
00:19:51.773 --> 00:19:53.150 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>From the very start,</i>

304
00:19:53.692 --> 00:19:56.111 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Ms. Waguri has always been upfront</i>
<i>and honest with me.</i>

305
00:19:59.198 --> 00:20:01.950 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>So I've got to do the same.</i>

306
00:20:04.369 --> 00:20:08.498 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When my friends at Chidori
bad-mouth Kikyo,

307
00:20:09.082 --> 00:20:11.168 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I usually don't think much of it.

308
00:20:12.044 --> 00:20:15.839 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'd accepted that our two schools
hate each other.

309
00:20:17.090 --> 00:20:20.677 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But when I thought of them
bad-mouthing you,

310
00:20:21.470 --> 00:20:22.512 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I couldn't accept it.

311
00:20:23.722 --> 00:20:25.224 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I hated it.

312
00:20:25.307 --> 00:20:29.144 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But I was worried that if you got involved
with me, I'd just put you in danger.

313
00:20:29.228 --> 00:20:30.854 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So I held back.

314
00:20:34.483 --> 00:20:37.611 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Please let me undo
what I took back earlier.

315
00:20:37.694 --> 00:20:41.615 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm sorry I was so focused on our schools
that I wasn't paying attention to you.

316
00:20:41.698 --> 00:20:43.825 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I was happy too!

317
00:20:54.962 --> 00:20:56.964 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ms. Waguri?

318
00:20:57.923 --> 00:21:00.217 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm fine now! Sorry for worrying you!

319
00:21:03.387 --> 00:21:04.513 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Rintaro.

320
00:21:05.847 --> 00:21:07.849 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm Kaoruko Waguri.

321
00:21:08.350 --> 00:21:10.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I… I know.

322
00:21:12.562 --> 00:21:15.983 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And you are Rintaro Tsumugi.

323
00:21:19.069 --> 00:21:21.405 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Chidori and Kikyo don't matter.

324
00:21:23.282 --> 00:21:25.701 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Because it's you, Rintaro Tsumugi,

325
00:21:25.784 --> 00:21:28.245 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
that I wanted to get to know.

326
00:21:45.095 --> 00:21:49.016 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Sorry about suddenly</i>
<i>closing the curtains yesterday.</i>

327
00:21:49.099 --> 00:21:51.268 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I'm sure that came off as rude.</i>

328
00:21:51.351 --> 00:21:53.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Oh, I wasn't bothered by that at all!</i>

329
00:21:55.439 --> 00:21:56.315 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>That reminds me!</i>

330
00:21:56.398 --> 00:21:59.776 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>It's still early, so no one should be</i>
<i>in the classrooms right now, right?</i>

331
00:21:59.860 --> 00:22:01.903 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Yeah, probably not.</i>

332
00:22:03.280 --> 00:22:04.114 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Then…</i>

333
00:22:24.092 --> 00:22:25.761 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I wanna get to know you…</i>

334
00:22:27.054 --> 00:22:28.847 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Ms. Waguri.</i>

335
00:22:32.059 --> 00:22:35.270 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>A world I once thought</i>
<i>I'd never have anything to do with.</i>

336
00:22:36.480 --> 00:22:39.649 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Now it feels like</i>
<i>it's gotten a bit closer.</i>

337
00:22:39.733 --> 00:22:41.985 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
EPISODE 2
CHIDORI AND KIKYO

338
00:24:09.948 --> 00:24:11.950 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
